They first looked at what defines a habitable zone in a solar system. Planets are considered habitable when they have liquid water, which is considered the keystone of life. Liquid water only forms on planets that sit within a certain zone around its star. As habitable zones change due to stars evolving over time, a planet can get pushed out of the zone. If it ends up too far away, its water becomes ice.
